Quality entertainment coming up!

29
00:04:48,047 --> 00:04:50,167
Got one!

30
00:04:50,277 --> 00:04:52,247
Nishi!

31
00:06:29,277 --> 00:06:32,867
Nishi, remember when we found a stray dog?

32
00:06:33,277 --> 00:06:34,717
In kindergarten?

33
00:06:35,317 --> 00:06:38,077
And you said you'd take care of it?

34
00:06:38,617 --> 00:06:41,147
That made me so happy!

35
00:06:41,257 --> 00:06:42,727
Yeah?

36
00:06:43,327 --> 00:06:46,317
I'm gonna take him home with me.

37
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:49,257
You will? Thank you!

38
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:52,817
I already have a sea-monkey, so it'll be fine!

39
00:06:54,297 --> 00:06:58,467
Wanna see? C'mon, I'll show ya!

40
00:06:59,007 --> 00:07:00,237
Myon.

41
00:07:01,477 --> 00:07:03,377
So this is the new plot!

42
00:07:04,177 --> 00:07:06,007
In the far, distant future,

43
00:07:06,117 --> 00:07:10,607
where the world is starving from
over-population and environmental destruction,

44
00:07:11,417 --> 00:07:15,587
Earth decides to send
a spaceship in search for food.

45
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:21,327
But something goes wrong.

46
00:07:23,997 --> 00:07:25,987
They land on a strange planet.

47
00:07:26,097 --> 00:07:30,837
There's water and oxygen,
but nothing edible for humans!

48
00:07:34,337 --> 00:07:37,007
Except for one thing, they soon discover.

49
00:07:42,347 --> 00:07:45,407
A certain creature's poo.

50
00:07:46,557 --> 00:07:47,917
Ooh, gross!

51
00:07:49,287 --> 00:07:51,457
And it's the perfect food for humans.

52
00:07:51,457 --> 00:07:52,687
"It's delicious!"
And it's the perfect food for humans.

53
00:07:54,697 --> 00:07:58,427
But the creature's unbelievably bad at hunting
and on the verge of extinction!

54
00:07:58,597 --> 00:08:00,127
There's only one?

55
00:08:01,437 --> 00:08:05,137
Our men help the creature hunt, look after it!

56
00:08:05,637 --> 00:08:10,337
And they live like that for a while
until a new enemy arrives.

57
00:08:11,347 --> 00:08:16,177
Higher species of plants begin to fight
for food, which is also creature chips!

58
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:18,117
A poo-war, huh?

59
00:08:18,657 --> 00:08:21,717
But what happens then? The crew?

60
00:08:23,687 --> 00:08:26,817
Guess we need to send them home safely, huh?

61
00:08:27,327 --> 00:08:30,787
The planet is ideal in its own way, but...

62
00:08:32,297 --> 00:08:36,497
In fact, the planet's some kind of cell!

63
00:08:36,607 --> 00:08:40,197
Our crew must've ended up there
after being shrunk!

64
00:08:40,307 --> 00:08:41,497
A cell?

65
00:08:41,607 --> 00:08:43,737
Yeah, of a human body.

66
00:08:43,847 --> 00:08:45,007
Whose?

67
00:08:45,377 --> 00:08:46,037
Yours.

68
00:08:46,147 --> 00:08:47,447
Mine?

69
00:08:47,717 --> 00:08:52,177
Let's just say... it was the leader's fault.

70
00:08:52,757 --> 00:08:58,317
His love for his girl,
his determination to find that planet,

71
00:08:58,427 --> 00:09:01,557
his desperation led the ship there.

72
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:07,057
But one day, they realize
their bodies have grown bigger.

73
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:08,427
Why?

74
00:09:08,567 --> 00:09:09,897
Wonder why!

75
00:09:11,677 --> 00:09:16,007
And they hear a voice! From inside your tummy
as you're sitting in the toilet.

76
00:09:16,107 --> 00:09:19,407
"Oh my God!
We're growing bigger and bigger!"

77
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:21,347
Yikes!

78
00:09:21,447 --> 00:09:26,047
But they can communicate that way.
And they realize their inside your stomach.

79
00:09:26,157 --> 00:09:27,417
- Then what?
- They've gotta get out!

80
00:09:27,517 --> 00:09:30,247
- From where?
- At this point, they're moving along the colon!

81
00:09:30,357 --> 00:09:31,587
Not happening!!

82
00:09:31,857 --> 00:09:35,157
But what else can they do?
They keep getting bigger.

83
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:36,487
Your belly'll explode!

84
00:09:36,597 --> 00:09:39,537
- I said no!
- "We're almost out, don't flush us!"

85
00:09:39,637 --> 00:09:41,157
I AM flushing them!

86
00:09:41,637 --> 00:09:43,607
"We're out! We're out!"

87
00:09:44,507 --> 00:09:46,027
NO!!!

88
00:11:32,777 --> 00:11:34,477
Myon!

89
00:11:34,577 --> 00:11:36,277
Nishi!

90
00:11:36,387 --> 00:11:40,147
Nishi! Myon!!

91
00:11:40,587 --> 00:11:41,887
We're up here!

92
00:11:41,987 --> 00:11:43,617
You guys OK?

93
00:11:43,727 --> 00:11:45,347
A-OK!

94
00:11:45,857 --> 00:11:50,297
I'm relieved! We were worried!

95
00:11:50,397 --> 00:11:53,797
That was a surprise attack! So sudden!

96
00:12:11,857 --> 00:12:16,347
Told ya so! It's wicked, man!
A miracle, I say!

97
00:12:16,457 --> 00:12:20,047
The Other World by Robin Nishi.
The guy's a fucking genius!

98
00:12:20,697 --> 00:12:25,287
Cut class and meet me at the arcade!
The Strawberry Plaza in ten!

99
00:12:25,397 --> 00:12:26,797
Roger that.

100
00:12:27,137 --> 00:12:29,937
This place's so commercial.

101
00:12:30,537 --> 00:12:32,297
Dude, chill...

102
00:12:37,207 --> 00:12:38,697
Isn't that...

103
00:12:38,877 --> 00:12:41,867
Robin Nishi!!!

104
00:12:42,847 --> 00:12:44,877
"R! Nishi Book Signing"

105
00:12:45,017 --> 00:12:47,217
Check out the chicks!

106
00:12:47,317 --> 00:12:49,377
Fuckin' cool!

107
00:12:49,487 --> 00:12:52,117
Excuse me, you're Robin Nishi, right?

108
00:12:52,227 --> 00:12:54,387
Hiroshi, you idiot!!

109
00:12:56,897 --> 00:12:57,887
Fuck yeah!!

110
00:13:10,277 --> 00:13:11,577
Sorry!!

111
00:13:11,847 --> 00:13:12,967
We're huge fans!

112
00:13:13,077 --> 00:13:15,807
The Other World rocks!!

113
00:13:18,757 --> 00:13:20,687
Wanna grab a bite?

114
00:13:20,957 --> 00:13:21,817
Follow me!!

115
00:13:21,927 --> 00:13:23,647
Seriously?!

116
00:13:26,557 --> 00:13:27,257
Eat!

117
00:13:27,357 --> 00:13:29,327
Yes!!

118
00:13:30,227 --> 00:13:32,667
- This is like, your average day??
- Yeah!

119
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:36,167
- Awesome!
- I feel so alive!

120
00:13:36,267 --> 00:13:38,467
Robin, I'll pick up the tab!

121
00:13:38,707 --> 00:13:40,177
What're you talking about?

122
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:41,677
Hiroshi, you idiot!!

123
00:13:47,347 --> 00:13:50,807
Hiroshi, kids shouldn't worry
about things like that.

124
00:13:51,047 --> 00:13:53,147
Have fun and become a man!

125
00:13:53,957 --> 00:13:57,517
Not a clone, but someone who transcends!!

126
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:07,437
First contact with aliens!

127
00:14:07,537 --> 00:14:13,067
And directing this epic moment
is the artist who made it all possible...

128
00:14:13,177 --> 00:14:16,837
Salvatore Antonio Yang Gogh!!

129
00:14:32,627 --> 00:14:36,257
"HELLO"

130
00:14:36,727 --> 00:14:42,067
The crowd's cheers've gone up a notch here
at the 1st Cosmic Swimming Contest.

131
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:45,507
Representing Earth!
Matt Beyond Thorpe Myon!!!

132
00:14:47,737 --> 00:14:52,197
And so the race begins
as we witness history in the making!

133
00:14:55,077 --> 00:14:59,537
First corner and into the gate!
Cameras are not allowed inside!

134
00:15:07,497 --> 00:15:10,517
And they're coming out! 4 in the first group!
And she's there!

135
00:15:10,627 --> 00:15:13,727
Matt Beyond Thorpe Myon,
representing Earth!!!

136
00:15:16,867 --> 00:15:19,267
Isn't this supposed to be extinct?

137
00:15:23,977 --> 00:15:25,037
This one too!

138
00:16:52,387 --> 00:16:57,827
"To Yang and Myon"

139
00:17:22,757 --> 00:17:23,717
Think we can get out of here?

140
00:17:23,817 --> 00:17:24,847
Want to?

141
00:17:25,287 --> 00:17:27,947
We might be happier here.

142
00:17:46,147 --> 00:17:47,437
Jump!

143
00:18:09,037 --> 00:18:13,127
That's odd and it wasn't even time yet.

144
00:18:15,907 --> 00:18:19,937
Good God! I was about to go fetch you!

145
00:18:23,917 --> 00:18:25,037
