147
00:18:32,257 --> 00:18:35,347
The water level's increasing.

148
00:18:36,197 --> 00:18:39,317
And he's eating less.

149
00:18:39,767 --> 00:18:41,127
Meaning?

150
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:47,497
Can't say for sure, but he could be dying.

151
00:18:48,107 --> 00:18:52,337
Dying? But what happens to us then?

152
00:18:52,747 --> 00:18:55,267
Eventually, this place'll sink.

153
00:18:58,317 --> 00:19:01,377
We've gotta leave. It's that or drown.

154
00:19:01,487 --> 00:19:03,047
But how?

155
00:19:03,157 --> 00:19:04,917
The boat, of course!

156
00:19:05,017 --> 00:19:07,857
- The cops'll be looking for us.
- So?

157
00:19:07,957 --> 00:19:10,427
The Yakuzas'll come after us!

158
00:19:10,527 --> 00:19:13,117
So what! I wanna get out!

159
00:19:13,927 --> 00:19:15,657
'Cos there's so much out there!

160
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:19,027
So many different people,
living different lives!

161
00:19:19,137 --> 00:19:21,697
Incredibly good guys, bad guys...

162
00:19:21,807 --> 00:19:25,867
Folks completely different from us!
It's one huge melting pot!

163
00:19:26,277 --> 00:19:30,607
See, it's not about success,
dying in the streets, who's better, who's not!

164
00:19:30,717 --> 00:19:32,947
I just want to be a part of it!

165
00:19:33,187 --> 00:19:36,677
I realized that even if I've no connections,
no talent,

166
00:19:36,857 --> 00:19:38,787
even if I'm one big loser,

167
00:19:38,887 --> 00:19:43,627
